            "sourceData": {
              "fabricAnswer": "Here are the latest sales trends based on available product and category data:\n\n- Electrical category: Sales generally increase through spring and early summer, peaking again in October and November before a slight dip in December. This category shows cyclic monthly changes with sharper growth in the last quarter of the year.\n\n- Garden & Outdoor: There is a significant sales spike in March and April, likely due to seasonal demand as gardening activities pick up. Sales gradually decrease through the summer and fall, with the lowest sales in winter months.\n\n- Hand Tools (trend begun): January shows strong sales. For more months or trends in this category, additional data would be needed.\n\nOverall, seasonal effects are notable—categories like \"Garden & Outdoor\" rise sharply in spring, while \"Electrical\" maintains steady growth with notable late-year increases. These trends indicate strong seasonality and highlight the importance of category-driven sales changes.",
